-- Hancock succeeds Benmosche as AIG's CEO and president
-- 
-- Mon Sep 01, 2014 08:19AM EDT
-- None



Sept 1 (Reuters) - American International Group <AIG.N> on Monday said that Peter Hancock has assumed the role of President and Chief Executive Officer, replacing Robert Benmosche.

Benmosche, originally scheduled to retire in 2015, was diagnosed with cancer in 2010. He learned in May that he had nine months to a year to live. [ID:nL3N0QY4UL] Benmosche will now serve as an advisor, the company said in a statement. [ID:nBw2RZMTCa]